<snippet>
	<content><![CDATA[const maxN = (arr, n = 1) => [...arr].sort((a, b) => b - a).slice(0, n);]]></content>
	<description>Returns the `n` maximum elements from the provided array. If `n` is greater than or equal to the provided array's length, then return the original array(sorted in descending order).  Use `Array.sort()` combined with the spread operator (`...`) to create a shallow clone of the array and sort it in descending order. Use `Array.slice()` to get the specified number of elements. Omit the second argument, `n`, to get a one-element array.</description>
